## 🧩 Moral Rights (Berne Convention Art. 6bis)

Moral rights are distinct from economic rights and **cannot be waived by contract** in most EU Member States:

| Right | Description | AI Implication |
|---|---|---|
| Right of attribution | Author must be identified | AI outputs that present extracted content must attribute the source author/publisher |
| Right of integrity | No distortion or mutilation of work | AI must not produce outputs that distort the meaning or context of extracted content |
| Right of disclosure | Author controls first publication | AI may not publish unpublished works without consent |

**Rules for AI Development:**

- **RULE**: Always include source attribution in extracted rules, plans, and excerpts
- **RULE**: Paraphrased content must not distort the original meaning of the source document
- **RULE**: Never present AI-derived content as if it originates from the document author without proper attribution

